---
import KlikboxSeoAiLayout from "../../layouts/KlikboxSeoAiLayout.astro";
---
<KlikboxSeoAiLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Klikbox SEO AI"
  description="Privacy policy for Klikbox SEO AI, a Shopify app by Klikbox."
>
  <section class="legal-page">
    <article class="legal-card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: May 24, 2026</p>

      <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        Klikbox SEO AI is a Shopify app operated by Klikbox. Our website is
        <a href="https://klikbox.gr">https://klikbox.gr</a>. For privacy questions,
        contact <a href="mailto:klikboxofficial@gmail.com">klikboxofficial@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Information the app accesses</h2>
      <p>
        Klikbox SEO AI accesses product catalog data needed to provide its core SEO
        workflow. This can include product titles, handles, descriptions, product SEO
        titles, product SEO descriptions, product status, and product IDs.
      </p>
      <p>
        The app does not request protected customer data for its current functionality.
        It does not read customer profiles, orders, payment details, or buyer records.
      </p>

      <h2>3. How we use information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To audit product SEO fields and product description length.</li>
        <li>To generate draft SEO copy for merchant review.</li>
        <li>To apply product updates only when the merchant approves a draft.</li>
        <li>To show draft history and monthly usage inside the app.</li>
        <li>To provide support and troubleshoot app issues.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. AI processing</h2>
      <p>
        When a merchant generates a draft, selected product information and brand voice
        instructions may be sent to OpenAI to create product SEO draft copy. We do not
        intentionally send customer records, payment data, or order data to OpenAI.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Data storage</h2>
      <p>
        The app stores Shopify session data needed to keep the app installed and
        authenticated. It also stores usage records, brand voice settings, and draft
        history so merchants can review recent activity.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Sharing information</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell merchant or buyer data. We share information only with service
        providers needed to operate the app, such as hosting providers, Shopify, and
        OpenAI for AI draft generation.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Security</h2>
      <p>
        The production app is intended to run over HTTPS. Access tokens and API keys
        are stored server-side and are not exposed in the browser.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Data retention and deletion</h2>
      <p>
        We retain app data only as needed to provide the service, support merchants,
        meet legal obligations, and maintain app security. When a store uninstalls the
        app, we process Shopify uninstall events and stop using the store access token.
      </p>
      <p>
        Merchants can request deletion of stored app data by emailing
        <a href="mailto:klikboxofficial@gmail.com">klikboxofficial@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Merchant rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on location, merchants may have rights to access, correct, delete,
        or restrict processing of personal data. To make a request, contact us by email.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy as the app changes. The updated policy will be posted
        on this page with a new last updated date.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Email: <a href="mailto:klikboxofficial@gmail.com">klikboxofficial@gmail.com</a><br />
        Website: <a href="https://klikbox.gr">https://klikbox.gr</a>
      </p>
    </article>

    <aside class="aside">
      <h3>Summary</h3>
      <p>The app uses product catalog data to audit and draft product SEO copy.</p>
      <p>No protected customer data is requested for the current app workflow.</p>
      <p class="meta">This page is for Shopify App Store submission and merchant transparency.</p>
    </aside>
  </section>
</KlikboxSeoAiLayout>
